an 82yearold lawmaker of the ruling 
nationalist party died one day after fainting in the legislature 
building while rioters outside called for him and other elderly 
lawmakers to quit 
chiang kungliang died of a lung malfunction wednesday evening 
at the national taiwan university hospital 
chiang who had been hospitalized for a year with asthma 
fainted tuesday as the legislature convened to vote for a new 
speaker 
a hospital statement did not say if chiangs death was related 
to the rioting outside 
but a doctor for the legislature speaking on condition of 
anonymity said the death may have been partly caused by shock over 
the violent protest 
chiang was among the more than 100 lawmakers who last faced 
election on the chinese mainland more than four decades ago they 
have been frozen in office in support of the nationalist 
governments claim to still be the legitimate ruler of all china 
the protesters demanded that the aging legislators be replaced 
by people elected in taiwan 
in the rioting more than 100 people were injured including 
five elderly politicians who were punched and kicked by the 
demonstrators 
