such reductions would be highly unusual for the us military 
which following world war ii the korean war and vietnam was able 
to slim its ranks by turning loose thousands of draftees eager to 
reenter the civilian economy todays soldiers and officers 
however are all volunteers and for many the service is a career 
in a joint introductory passage in the army report stone and 
vuono said movements away from totalitarian rule in the soviet 
union and eastern europe had opened the way to what may be a 
significant reduction in the possibility of war between major 
industrialized nations 
