here is a summary of communications between 
pilots of avianca flight 52 and air traffic controllers prior to 
the jan 25 crash that killed 73 people at cove neck ny as 
disclosed in national transportation safety board urgent 
recommendations on the crash 
844 pm air traffic controllers tell the plane to expect 
clearance to continue on at 905 pm the response is ah well 
i think we need priority were passing out of garbled the 
controller roger how long can you hold and what is your 
alternative airport the plane crew replies yes sir well 
be able to hold about five minutes thats all we can do 
846 pm a controller at new york air traffic control center 
advises another control center new york tracon that avianca 52 
can only do five more minutes in the hold do you think you can 
take him or should i offer him his alternate the second 
controller says slow him to one eight zero knots and i will take 
him into kennedy airport 
at the same time the flight crew advises the first controller 
who has asked for his alternate airport it was boston but we 
cant do it now we ah we will run out of fuel now 
856 pm the plane is instructed by a controller to turn 
right right turn heading two twenty im going to have to spin you 
make a 360degree turn sir 
903 pm during the next seven minutes avianca 52 receives 
routine radar service including several heading changes and 
further clearances in its descent into kennedy 
911 pm the final controller youre on five miles from 
the marker maintain two thousands till established on localizer 
cleared runway 22 left 
915 pm the flight crew is instructed to contact kennedy 
airport tower the tower tells avianca it was no 3 to land 
923 pm avianca 52 advises the kennedy tower it is executing 
a missed approached 
924 pm the flight crew ah well try once again were 
running out of fuel controller okay 
925 pm avianca acknowledging instructions from the final 
controller climb and maintain three thousand and uh were 
running out of fuel sir controller okay ah fly a heading 
of zero eight zero im going to bring you about fifteen miles 
northeast and then turn you back on for the approach is that fine 
with you and your fuel the response i guess so thank you 
very much 
929 pm when can you give us a final asks avianca the 
final controller responds affirmative turn left heading zero 
four zero 
930 pm after the controller clears the plane to maintain 
3000 feet the flight crew says ah negative sir we just 
running out of fuel we okay three thousand 
932 pm from avianca we just lost two engines and we need 
priority please the controller advises the plane that it is 15 
miles from the airport outer marker and clears it for approach to 
runway 22 left 
934 pm the controller you have ah you have enough fuel 
to make it to the airport 
avianca 52 did not respond 
