while the winter wheat crop in the southern plains was 
stressed by dryness in the fall and early winter precipitation and 
relatively mild temperatures in january and february have raised 
crop prospects the report said nonetheless timely rains will 
be needed in coming months 
looking at the global situation the report said wheat export 
prices in recent weeks have declined to below yearearlier levels 
rising foreign stocks relatively slow sales in the first half 
of the 198990 marketing year a largerthananticipated southern 
hemisphere harvest and prospects for a large 199091 northern 
hemisphere crop have translated into the declining export prices 
the report said 
overall global wheat production in 198990 is up about 7 
percent from a year earlier but consumption will exceed production 
for the third straight year that will drain world wheat stockpiles 
to their lowest level since 198182 
but all of the decline in global wheat inventories will be in 
the united states the report said stocks held by foreign exporters 
are up 12 percent from the 198989 marketing year 
