voluntary recall the agency said it was opening a formal safety 
defect investigation to prepare for a possible governmentordered 
recall 
the probe covers 175000 chevrolet camaros and pontiac firebirds 
from the 1982 through 1986 model years it also covers 273000 
pontiac fieros from the 1984 through 1986 model years 
rear disc brakes on many of the vehicles do not adjust 
automatically as the brake pads wear the agency said in a 
statement 
as a result the rear brakes may become less effective in 
stopping a moving car and the parking brake may be unable to hold 
a parked car on a slope it said there are no warning signs of 
the parking brake problem 
the brake warning light might be activated depending on the 
extent of brake pad wear and how hard the driver presses the pedal 
but it sometimes illuminates only during emergency stops when the 
driver is exerting full force on the brake the statement said 
a vehicle typically develops the problem after about 18600 
miles on the road 
the agency said it received 42 complaints from owners including 
