colombia peru and bolivia us officials agreed to provide aid 
in developing other crops peru produces most of the worlds coca 
which is processed into cocaine and bolivia grows about onethird 
of it 
the agriculture department research program was reported tuesday 
by the washington post and white house press secretary marlin 
fitzwater said later we are not undertaking any biological war 
neither troops nor caterpillars will go in without prior request 
and consultation 
more than 300000 farmers in bolivia and 200000 in peru depend 
on coca for their livelihood peru estimates sales of the leaves 
bring 1 billion into the country each year and bolivia earns up 
to 500 million a year from coca 
bolivian farmers have destroyed 4940 acres of coca plants since 
