predicted that official chinese contacts with the us embassy in 
beijing would drop off sharply 
the embassy experienced similarly chilly relations with many 
chinese government units in the first months after the armys june 
34 crackdown on prodemocracy protesters in beijing 
official newspapers then carried daily attacks on the united 
states for criticizing the armys killing of hundreds of 
protesters and for sheltering dissidents fang lizhi and his wife 
however relations began improving in the last months of 1989 
following visits of former president richard nixon and scowcroft 
the official response to the state department report said the 
report was based on guesses and rumors 
the repeated acts of grossly interfering in chinas internal 
affairs are but expressions of outandout hegemonism and power 
politics it said 
