secretary the sessions were primarily getacquainted talks 
with each side laying out for the other their global views in light 
of the revolutionary changes that have swept eastern europe and the 
soviet union williams said 
the officials found that they shared very similar views 
williams said both taking a very cautious approach to events 
in the soviet union 
