for delaying the release of the testimony 
the press and the public were not admitted to the deposition 
itself but in view of the requirement of openness of crimnal 
proceedings this segment of the poindexter criminal trial should 
not be kept secret the judge said the public is entitled to 
know now to what the former president testified 
on wednesday the justice department said it would not seek to 
delete any portions of the reagan tapes indicating they did 
contain any sensitive or classified information 
