<TEXT>
czechoslovak president vaclav havel started his 
new york visit today with breakfast at the mayors mansion where 
the former dissident playwright was joined by a number of us 
writers 
the breakfast with mayor david dinkins was the first item on a 
busy schedule that included lunch with human rights advocates a 
stop at an art museum and meetings with the council on foreign 
relations czechoslovakamericans and un secretarygeneral javier 
perez de cuellar 
havel a former jailed dissident who was elected czechoslovak 
president dec 29 arrived in the united states on monday he spoke 
to a joint meeting of the house and the senate on wednesday and met 
with president bush twice 
havels wife olga havlova did not attend todays breakfast 
havel said she was tired from their travels guests at the 
breakfast included writers kurt vonnegut edward albee and arthur 
miller 
havel said as a playwright he never could have conceived a plot 
in which he would become president 
it is extremely strange and extraordinary he said but i 
dont have time to think about it it is a busy job to be 
president 
after breakfast producer joseph papp presented havel with a 
collage and said he would produce the czechoslovak presidents 
play slum clearance 
dinkins gave havel a crystal apple and kitty carlisle hart 
chairwoman of the state council of the arts and a former actress 
gave him a copy of act one the autobiography of her late 
husband playwright moss hart 
havel said he was extremely happy to be once more in new 
york he was last in new york in 1968 for the first night of one 
of his plays 
asked to compare his ascent to office and dinkins campaign to 
become the citys first black mayor havel said one difference 
i didnt want to be a president but i was raised to the post by 
public pressure i didnt want it personally 
the czechoslovak parliament elected havel president a few weeks 
after a peaceful revolution that led to the ouster of a hardline 
communist government havels caretaker government is preparing for 
parliamentary elections in june 
havels next stop was the metropolitan museum of art he was 
greeted on the museum steps by two dozen flagwaving cheering 
youngsters from the czechoslovak school for children of 
czechoslovakian diplomats 
theyve looked forward to this for months and months 
teacher lida husek said for us the changes in our country are 
very exciting but were so far from home this is our way of 
keeping in touch with him and with our countrymen 
he then traveled to cardinal john oconnors residence where he 
received a crystal star from the president of the appeal of 
conscience foundation rabbi arthur schneier 
on wednesday havel told congress that the united states could 
best help his country by pressing the soviet union to stay on its 
own road to democracy havel was the first of the new east european 
leaders to address congress 
speaking through a translator havel called czechoslovakia one 
of eastern europes wayward children and said it wants to 
coordinate its return to the economic and political mainstream with 
hungary poland and other nations emerging from 40 years of soviet 
domination 
