of islamic and humanitarian considerations should work to get the 
hostages free with no precondition the englishlanguage tehran 
times said in an editorial parts of which were carried by irans 
official islamic republic news agency 
it was the first known statement by an iranian newspaper in 
support of freeing all the hostages whose fate is believed linked 
to a power struggle within the iranian government 
eight americans four britons an irishman an italian two west 
germans and two swiss citizens are captives in lebanon 
terry a anderson 42 has been held the longest he is chief 
middle east correspondent of the associated press and was abducted 
march 16 1985 
