ailment complaining of sore throats headaches or dizziness other 
symptoms that have afflicted workers since the outbreak began feb 
16 include vomiting watery eyes and fainting one worker required 
mouthtomouth resuscitation 
carbon monoxide poisoning was ruled out on wednesday on 
thursday test results showed that tap and bottled water were not 
the problem officials said 
