the agreement reached at a meeting of nato and warsaw pact 
foreign ministers last week in ottawa canada is to be part of a 
final accord on reducing manpower tanks artillery and other 
nonnuclear arms in europe which negotiators hope to conclude this 
year 
ruediger hartmann the chief west german delegate said in his 
statement to the final session the negotiations are now moving at 
a rate commensurate with the rapidity of political processes in 
europe according to a text made available to journalists 
hungary and czechoslovakia are negotiating for total withdrawal 
of soviet troops from their territory they and poland have 
announced reductions in their own armed forces 
about 50000 soviet military personnel are stationed in hungary 
and 75000 in czechoslovakia 
ernst said the overall ceiling suggested by the kremlin would 
include national armies and soviet troops stationed on foreign soil 
