<TEXT>
nasa on thursday delayed the launch 
of atlantis for a second day to let the shuttles commander recover 
from a sore throat and to await better weather 
the secret military mission to put a spy satellite in orbit is 
not expected to take off until saturday morning at the earliest 
the shuttle originally was scheduled for a predawn liftoff 
thursday but was postponed wednesday when navy capt john o 
creighton became ill the second time the space program has delayed 
a flight because of a sick astronaut 
nasa delayed the launch yet another day on the recommendation of 
doctors examining creighton who complained of a sore throat and 
congestion 
physicians report that his condition has improved but 
that he still has some infection of the upper respiratory tract 
the space agency said in a statement additionally weather 
conditions presently are not expected to be satisfactory for 
fueling required for a morning launch 
nasa said it would decide whether to proceed with a saturday 
launch after examining creighton and the forecast on friday 
saturdays outlook was a scant 20 percent chance for liftoff 
because of an approaching cold front but that was to improve to 70 
percent by sunday 
in 1969 the apollo 9 mission to orbit the earth and test the 
lunar landing module was delayed three days after the three crewmen 
got sick 
nasa said it had no plans to replace creighton on the mission 
because his illness was not serious responding in writing to 
reporters questions nasa flight surgeons said the prognosis is 
good but they didnt say when the commander might be able to fly 
creighton was quarantined and the four other crew members were 
healthy and isolated the doctors said changes in cabin 
pressure normally experienced in flight would cause creighton pain 
in his present condition they said 
the delays came before technicians had begun pumping more than 
half a million gallons of propellant into atlantis fuel tank for 
the fourday mission which was to end at edwards force base calif 
pumping the fuel would have added 377000 to the cost to 
kennedy space center of delaying the mission each days delay 
costs 247000 in labor and materials that does not include 
expenses at other nasa centers supporting the mission 
sources said atlantis cargo is a 37300pound 500 million 
satellite capable of taking supersharp photos and eavesdropping on 
electronic communications around the world its path will carry it 
over most of the soviet union 
nasa has not announced a precise launch time since atlantis 
cargo is classified but sources who spoke on condition of 
anonymity said it would take place around 1 am 
atlantis flight will be the 34th shuttle flight and the sixth 
secret military mission 
</TEXT>
