united arab emirates and abu musa an iranian island 
cohen said some work was being done on one of the ships 
starboard cargo tanks about midway down the 700foot deck where 
the explosion occurred he said the missing men were in the area 
the simpson on patrol three miles away was observing the surf 
city visually and on radar officials said the missile destroyer 
uss dewey another of the 10 us warships on duty in the gulf 
also went to the scene as did several patrol craft and helicopters 
from the emirates 
a statement from the kuwait oil tanker co said the fire spread 
quickly from the blast point toward the stern where the engine 
room bridge and crews quarters are located 
it said the tanker was listing and salvage tugs were trying to 
recover it shipping executives said the tugs were forced to stay 
clear because of the fire 
