<TEXT>
the government posted its first monthly budget 
surplus of fiscal 1990 in january but the federal deficit after 
four months still totaled nearly 60 percent of the amount permitted 
for the entire year 
despite januarys 992 billion surplus the deficit for the 
first four months of the fiscal year totaled 5978 billion the 
treasury said thursday the grammrudman deficitreduction law 
limits the fiscal 1990 imbalance to 100 billion 
the deficit last year was 1521 billion 
the 1990 deficit through january was 77 percent lower than that 
for the first four months of fiscal 1989 januarys surplus 
contrasted with a 146 billion imbalance during december 
much of the surplus was due to a surge in revenue from 
individual income tax collections however the surplus also was 
inflated artificially by sampl bailout borrowing 
the treasury reported that individual tax receipts in january 
totaled 5604 billion up 50 percent from december collections 
individual income tax receipts are expected to remain high through 
the april 15 deadline for filing 1989 returns 
receipts were inflated in january by 5 billion borrowed through 
a special offbudget agency called the resolution funding corp 
normally government borrowing does not count as revenue 
overall receipts totaled 9954 billion in january up 115 
percent from january 1989 outlays were 8962 billion a 36 
percent increase over the same month a year ago the deficit is the 
difference between revenue and spending 
so far this fiscal year receipts totaled 3283 billion up 56 
