officials in central france said thursday bacteria 
had been cleared from drinking drinking water but authorities 
elsewhere warned pregnant women of nitrate pollution 
health officials in the eastern city of belfort told 20000 
residents to continue drinking bottled water or to add chlorine to 
tap water 
about 100000 residents of the region were told on wednesday not 
to drink tap water because bacteria resulting from last weeks 
heavy rains and flooding clouded the water officials now say the 
water should be safe to drink by saturday 
the problems have raised new worries about water pollution in 
france and the national environment minister has criticized farmers 
for their use of fertilizers 
in central france authorities at chateauroux and delos told 
60000 people a bacterial infestation had been cleared and lifted a 
fiveday ban on drinking tap water 
