1986 from the arms business and other income sources 
however the fourcount indictment returned by a federal grand 
jury in baltimore alleges that clines failed to report to the 
internal revenue service that he had foreign accounts totaling more 
than 10000 
two counts of the indictment accuse him of underreporting the 
gross receipts each count carries a maximum penalty of three years 
imprisonment and 100000 in fines on conviction 
the other counts accuse clines of failing to report his foreign 
accounts with maximum penalties on conviction for each charge of 
10 years in prison and 500000 in fines 
during the period in question hakim set aside more than 
