<TEXT>
an unmanned ariane 44l rocket with 
two japanese telecommunications satellites aboard exploded shortly 
after blasting off thursday from the ariane space center 
the fourengine rocket blew up because of what appeared to be a 
fire in the propulsion system but the precise cause was not 
immediately clear arianespace president frederic dallest said 
he said all ariane flights were being suspended until the cause 
of the accident was determined 
the failure came after 17 straight successful launches of the 
ariane the two satellites alone were insured for nearly 240 
million 
an associated press reporter and other witnesses who saw the 
flight on tv monitors at the agencys headquarters in evry france 
said flames appeared to break out in the first stage of the rocket 
before it was due to separate at two minutes 30 seconds into 
flight 
they also said that flames from one rocket booster unexpectedly 
burned into the scaffolding supporting the vehicle as it lifted 
off but there was no indication this had any bearing on the 
explosion 
a mishap in the function of the first stage led to the loss of 
mission flight 36 one minute 40 seconds into launch 
arianespace said in a statement released in paris 
the rocket exploded about 62 miles from the launch pad at an 
altitude of 56 miles the statement said 
we are going to analyze the failure as rapidly as 
possible said dallest 
arianespace a consortium of european companies took over the 
commercialization of the ariane program from the european space 
agency in 1980 it is responsible for building operating and 
marketing launch services 
ariane shots have become routine with successful missions about 
once a month the reliability of the program has made arianespace 
the worlds leading provider of commercial launch services holding 
more than 50 percent of the lucrative international market 
the french space minister paul quilles said the explosion 
should not cast doubt on the ariane program which he noted had had 
an exceptional run 
the risk of a failure is always present at each launch its 
part of the business quilles said 
the first stage of the threestage vehicle holds the strapon 
boosters fueled by a nitrogenoxygen compound that should have 
thrust the 190foot 582ton vehicle into orbit 
the rocket lifted off from this french overseas department in 
northeast south america at 817 pm local time 617 pm est 
tracing a graceful pattern over the launch site 
it was about six miles above the atlantic ocean when the blast 
ripped it apart dallest said wind blowing fuel back toward 
kourou forced residents to stay indoors 
thursdays launch was the 36th ariane mission since the first 
launch in the unmanned space program on on dec 24 1979 
the explosion was the first since the 18th ariane flight blew up 
may 31 1986 and the first of the rocket series since its maiden 
launch june 15 1988 
fortythree satellites have been launched and another 32 are 
scheduled for future launch with a contract value of 236 billion 
in all five ariane rockets have failed in flight previously 
the others were the second mission on may 23 1980 the fifth on 
sept 10 1982 in the presence of president francois mitterrand 
and the 15th on sept 13 1985 
