<TEXT>
a 1 billion project to deliver as many as 108 
channels of television programming via satellite to home dishes 
small enough to fit on a window sill is being developed by a group 
of four major media companies 
wednesdays announcement left plenty of unresolved questions 
about the service including what programs would be made available 
and how much the service would cost 
but there is no rush the service is not expected to debut until 
1993 
media industry analysts say the venture called sky cable would 
provide expanded choices for viewers encourage production of more 
tv programming and raise competition for cable operators 
but they also note that several obstacles remain including 
overcoming the industrys track record of failed directtohome 
satellite tv ventures in the united states 
the partners are general electric cos national broadcasting 
co rupert murdochs news corp ltd cablevision systems corp a 
cable system operator and programmer based in woodbury ny and 
hughes communications inc a satellite technology concern owned by 
general motors corp 
the partners said they had signed a memorandum of understanding 
for the venture which they said would be the first highpower 
direct broadcast satellite service 
they said the service would be competitively priced but 
specific program offerings had not been determined yet 
the service would be an addition to rather than a replacement 
for existing cable service they contended 
but some analysts disagreed peter appert who follows the media 
business for the investment firm cj lawrence morgan grenfell 
said sky cable poses a significant competitive threat to the 
cable industry 
if i can can get 108 channels priced competitively i dont 
see why i need cable if they can deliver as promised and the 
quality is as promised he said 
sky cable would use the most powerful satellites ever launched 
for commercial communications purposes and be capable of delivering 
both highdefinition television and standard video signals as well 
as digital quality audio 
the companies said the new venture likely would be the first to 
introduce hdtv to the united states on a broad scale 
the venture will cost about 1 billion including an equity 
investment of about 335 million each of the partners plan to 
contribute equal amounts of the equity once they reach a definitive 
agreement 
at a news conference the promoters displayed a receiving dish 
measuring 12 to 18 inches across that they said would be used for 
sky cable they said they expected the dish would cost about 300 
much less than the 2000 to 3000 price tag on bulkier 
conventional dishes 
a few programs would be available free of charge to dish owners 
but subscribers would have to pay for other programming which may 
include multichannel packages single channels and payperview 
programs 
this wont replace cable said charles dolan chairman and 
chief executive of cablevision 
dolan said cable operators will be asked to install service and 
handle billing for sky cable subscribers also will be able to sign 
up on their own 
previous efforts to launch directtohome service in the united 
states have made little headway such services are available in 
great britain and japan 
appert said past us efforts often failed because the receiving 
dish was cumbersome channel capacity was limited and the signal 
often was distorted 
earlier this month a group of nine us cable operators and 
ges american communications unit announced a venture to offer 10 
channels of programming later this year via a ge satellite 
robert thomson an executive at telecommunications inc the 
nations largest cable operator and a member of the cable group 
said the sky cable plans wont affect his groups satellite 
broadcast plans 
sky cable will be competitive to cable he said but cable 
companies have an advantage of a large programming and customer 
base and a flexible and secure transmission system 
news corp offers a satellitedelivered tv service in great 
britain but startup losses have been heavy murdoch said the 
british service has 600000 subscribers and needs 2 million to 
become profitable 
the american sky cable service will need between 3 million and 5 
million subscribers to break even murdoch said 
murdoch and robert wright president of nbc said there are no 
plans to offer their respective tv networks fox and nbc on the 
sky cable 
but cablevision and nbc jointly own the consumer news and 
business channel bravo sports channel america and 10 regional 
sports channels 
murdoch said his company may provide programming for sky cable 
news corp operations include twentieth century fox films and tv 
show production 
</TEXT>
