san jacinto savings and loan association has filed 
a 14 billion claim against its parent southmark corp saying the 
junkbond built company now in bankruptcy court forced it to make 
bad loans 
southmark had envisioned san jacinto as its core business after 
emerging from bankruptcy court proceedings southmark last month 
submitted a chapter 11 reorganization plan calling for the sale of 
nearly all assets except san jacinto 
southmark on thursday reported a net loss of 568 million on 
revenue of 267 million for its first quarter ending sept 30 
1989 that compared with net income of 114 million on revenue of 
561 million in the same 1988 period 
after allowing for a dividend on special stock the pershare 
results amount to a loss of 124 in the 1989 period against a loss 
of 20 cents in the 1988 period 
