administrative expenses plus 31 million in interest saved by the 
bankruptcy filing 
the report was delayed while the company formulated its 
reorganization plans a plan submitted in court last month called 
for retaining houstonbased san jacinto and turning over remainding 
assets to creditors after pumping an additional 100 million into 
the thrift 
but creditors wednesday called the plan unworkable and asked 
us bankruptcy judge steven felsenthal for permission to submit 
their own reorganization proposal that would surrender the thrift 
to regulators and quickly liquidate the remaining company 
a hearing on the creditors request to end southmarks exclusive 
right to propose a plan is scheduled for march 14 
san jacintos 14 billion claim against southmark seeks payment 
for 584 million in bad syndication loans guaranteed by southmark 
and as much as 376 million in loans made at the direction of the 
company 
san jacinto is the only large savings institution in texas that 
hasnt been seized or sold by federal regulators when southmark 
