million below regulators minimum levels san jacinto claims 
southmark owes another 274 million to meet the new riskbased 
capital requirements imposed by last years federal thrift bailout 
legislation 
the creditors claim the thrift is losing 10 million a month and 
is failing to meet its business plan according to court papers 
filed by a group of the companys creditors 
