<TEXT>
three measures of the nations money supply each 
rose in the week ended feb 12 the federal reserve board reported 
thursday 
the fed said the narrowest measure of the money supply m1 
edged up 100 million to a seasonally adjusted 7986 billion from 
a revised 7985 billion the previous week the prior week was 
initially reported at 7992 billion 
the central bank said the measure known as m2 rose 30 billion 
to a seasonally adjusted 32525 billion from a revised 32495 
billion the previous week the previous weeks figure had been 
reported at 32517 billion 
an even broader measure m3 rose 34 billion to a seasonally 
adjusted 40689 billion from 40655 billion the previous 
weeks figure was initially reported at 40678 billion 
m1 includes cash in circulation deposits in checking accounts 
and nonbank travelers checks m2 is m1 plus accounts like savings 
deposits and moneymarket mutual funds m3 is m2 plus lessliquid 
accounts such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations 
of 100000 
in judging its monetary policy the fed has indicated it is 
monitoring the value of the dollar commodity prices and the 
difference between short and longterm interest rates it also has 
shifted its attention from m1 to the two broader money supply 
measures 
the annual growth rate in m2 so far this year is 69 percent 
which is within the feds target range of 3 percent to 7 percent 
the annual growth rate in m3 is 42 percent also within the feds 
target range of 25 percent to 65 percent the fed has not set a 
target for m1 growth since early 1987 
for the latest 13 weeks m2 averaged 32262 billion a 49 
percent seasonally adjusted annual rate of gain from the previous 
13 weeks m3 averaged 40678 billion up 32 percent while m1 
rose 49 percent to an average of 7944 billion 
in other reports 
the federal reserve said bank borrowings from the federal 
reserve system at the discount window excluding extended credit 
averaged 1659 billion a day in the week ended wednesday up from 
1037 billion the previous week 
the federal reserve said net borrowed reserves averaged 355 
million in the latest two weeks compared with net free reserves of 
a revised 378 million in the previous twoweek period 
the federal reserve bank of st louis reported that the 
monetary base the seasonally adjusted total of member bank 
reserves held at federal reserve banks and cash in bank vaults and 
in circulation was 2985 billion in the latest twoweek period 
down from 3005 billion two weeks earlier 
