<TEXT>
stock prices ended mixed thursday in moderate 
trading after a lastminute selloff sparked by a rumor about a 
japanese scandal 
earlier issues rose following renewed strength on the tokyo 
market and buying by bargain hunters 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials closed down 879 to 
257477 at midday it had been up as much as 30 points 
advancing issues nearly matched declining issues in nationwide 
trading of new york stock exchangelisted stocks with 715 up 753 
down and 508 unchanged 
volume on the floor of the big board came to 18432 million 
shares up from 15924 million in the previous session 
nationwide consolidated volume in nyselisted issues including 
trades in those stocks on regional exchanges and in the 
overthecounter market totaled 21469 million shares 
in tokyo the key nikkei index was on a roller coaster until the 
close when it was up 9251 points or 025 percent to 3582684 
on wednesday the nikkei plummeted more than 3 percent for its 
thirdworst drop ever the plunge helped set off a tumble in london 
and new york but the us markets later recovered 
the market thursday also benefited from a firming in the price 
of us government debt securities analysts said and comments 
from federal reserve chairman alan greenspan greenspan told a 
senate committee that he sees no evidence inflation is accelerating 
and that it may be decreasing 
dudley eppel managing director of equity trading at donaldson 
lufkin amp jenrette securities corp said wall street exhibited 
optimism thursday until prices slipped in the last hour 
gordon l smith a managing director at alex brown amp sons inc 
a baltimore brokerage said computerized sell programs linked to 
stockindex futures kicked in during the last hour of trading 
selling also apparently was sparked by rumors of a stockrelated 
scandal in the japanese government he said the reports which 
smith called illdefined could not be confirmed or denied 
immediately 
philip morris one of the most active nyse issues was up to 
38lsqb the company said its kraft general foods division would 
aggressively seek acquisitions by about 1991 
union carbide another active bluechip issue was up 1lsqb at 23 
amid rumors of a possible takeover bid or the spinoff of a 
division the company declined to comment 
among other blue chips american telephone amp telegraph was down 
at 38lsqb ibm was down 1rsqb at 103 and general electric was up lsqb to 
60 
monsanto jumped 4rsqb to 112 on news that the food and drug 
administration approved the companys fat substitute for food 
products simplesse 
ual dropped 5 to 126 the wall street journal reported that 
the airline companys chairman stephen wolf decided not to back a 
unionled employee buyout that didnt include him 
pfizer another active nyse issue fell 4 to 59 on news 
reports that it could face a major productliability suit over a 
heart valve once sold by a subsidiary 
as measured by wilshire associates index of more than 5000 
actively traded stocks the market lost 1060 billion or 033 
percent in value 
the nyses composite index of all its listed common stocks 
dropped 079 to 18028 
standard amp poors industrial index lost 279 to 37535 and 
sampps 500stock composite index fell 197 to 32570 
the nasdaq composite index for the overthecounter market rose 
123 to 42275 at the american stock exchange the market value 
index gained 040 to 35335 
