<TEXT>
general motors corps chevrolet division said it 
has raised rebates from 500 to 1000 on 1989 and 1990 camaro and 
cavalier models delivered through may 2 
meanwhile rebates will be reduced from 750 to 500 on 1989 and 
1990 astro minivans delivered march 8 through may 2 chevrolet said 
wednesday in a statement 
buyers of those and certain other chevrolet cars and trucks may 
forgo rebates and opt for loan rates ranging from 69 percent to 
109 percent depending on the length of the contract the 
statement said 
